  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To determine if the use of automated office blood pressure readings can improve management of
      systolic hypertension in routine clinical practice. Automated office SBP recordings in
      routine clinical practice using the BpTRU device will reflect more accurately the mean awake
      ambulatory systolic BP than will manual BP readings taken with conventional mercury
      sphygmomanometry. This should lead to improvements in the management of systolic hypertension
      with optimization of drug therapy in practices using the BpTRU device.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
